Product-building is just not as easy as we think it is, both before and after it’s done. Before we start, it seems easier than it will be. And after we’re done, it seems easier than it was.
Cognitive Biases Whenever we build something, we face constraints:
We don’t know what problems to solve. And even if we knew that, we don’t know how to solve them. And even if we knew that, we don’t know how well we can deliver those solutions.
